{
  "texts": [
    "(The cover is finite since the deck transformations inject into the finite group G/G 0 = K/K 0.)",
    "By Theorem C, gauge equivalence classes of G 0 -Higgs bundles are in one-to-one correspondence with solutions of the twisted harmonic-Einstein equation for the pair (B 2, G 0 /K 0) up to equivalence.",
    "Moreover, solutions of the twisted harmonic-Einstein equation for the pair (B 2, G/K) are in one-to-one correspondence with solitons by Proposition 3.6.",
    "Hence, to prove Corollary D it suffices to show the following: Proposition 4.10.",
    "Let Σ = (B 2, c) be a Riemann surface, G a reductive group, and G 0 ≤ G its identity component."
  ]
}